{
  "page": "Wedding of Rhaena Targaryen and Androw Farman",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>wedding of Rhaena Targaryen and Androw Farman</b> occurred in <a href=\"/index.php/49_AC\" title=\"49 AC\">49&#160;AC</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Fair_Isle\" title=\"Fair Isle\">Fair Isle</a>. It was the first of three royal weddings that earned 49 AC the name the Year of the Three Brides.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Background\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Background</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Wedding\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Wedding</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Attendees\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Attendees</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background\">Background</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Background\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Before her wedding to <a href=\"/index.php/Androw_Farman\" title=\"Androw Farman\">Androw Farman</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a> was married twice before. The first was to her younger brother Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(son_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (son of Aenys I)\">Aegon Targaryen</a>. In <a href=\"/index.php/43_AC\" title=\"43 AC\">43&#160;AC</a>, Aegon was slain in <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_Beneath_the_Gods_Eye\" title=\"Battle Beneath the Gods Eye\">battle</a> by their uncle King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a> while attempting to claim the throne from him. After Prince Aegon's death, the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\">Farmans</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Fair_Isle\" title=\"Fair Isle\">Fair Isle</a> granted the widowed Rhaena refuge. While there, she grew fond of both Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Marq_Farman\" title=\"Marq Farman\">Marq Farman</a> and his younger son, <a href=\"/index.php/Androw_Farman\" title=\"Androw Farman\">Androw Farman</a>. In time, Maegor would summon Rhaena to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> to be one of his three \"<a href=\"/index.php/Black_Brides\" title=\"Black Brides\">Black Brides</a>.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> After Maegor's death, the twice-widowed Rhaena chose to return to Fair Isle rather than remain in King's Landing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Wedding\">Wedding</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Wedding\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman_by_MV_Renju_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4c/Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman_by_MV_Renju_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/300px-Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman_by_MV_Renju_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"399\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/4c/Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman_by_MV_Renju_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/450px-Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman_by_MV_Renju_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/4c/Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman_by_MV_Renju_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/600px-Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman_by_MV_Renju_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman_by_MV_Renju_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The wedding of Rhaena and Androw by MV Renju for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i></div></div></div>\n<p>Only a fortnight into the year <a href=\"/index.php/49_AC\" title=\"49 AC\">49&#160;AC</a>, Queen Rhaena Targaryen wed Androw Farman when she was twenty-six and he only seventeen. Androw was said to be utterly besotted with her. The ceremony was swift and small. Though two of Rhaena's former favorites, <a href=\"/index.php/Samantha_Stokeworth\" title=\"Samantha Stokeworth\">Samantha Stokeworth</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Alayne_Royce\" title=\"Alayne Royce\">Alayne Royce</a>, traveled to Fair Isle in haste to stand beside her, along with the groom's sister <a href=\"/index.php/Elissa_Farman\" title=\"Elissa Farman\">Elissa Farman</a>. Rhaena's kin were not notified. The ceremony was held under the sky, presided over by Lord Marq. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Lyman_Lannister\" title=\"Lyman Lannister\">Lyman Lannister</a> and his wife Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jocasta_Lannister\" title=\"Jocasta Lannister\">Jocasta Lannister</a> were the only great lords in attendance. The other guests were bannermen and household <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> sword to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\">House Farman</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a>. By the time a <a href=\"/index.php/Raven\" title=\"Raven\">raven</a> reached King's Landing with news of the marriage, the wedding feast and <a href=\"/index.php/Bedding\" title=\"Bedding\">bedding</a> to seal the match had already passed days before.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The bride's mother, Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alyssa_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyssa Velaryon\">Alyssa Velaryon</a>, was deeply offended at being neither informed of nor invited to her daughter's wedding, after which relationships between them were never as warm. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Rogar_Baratheon\" title=\"Rogar Baratheon\">Rogar Baratheon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> and soon-to-be second husband of Alyssa, was furious that Rhaena had remarried without his or the Crown's leave. One of his brothers and two of his nephews were as-yet unwed, which may explain Lord Rogar's fury. Rhaena's younger siblings, King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Targaryen\" title=\"Alysanne Targaryen\">Alysanne Targaryen</a>, rejoiced at the news and sent their gifts and congratulations to Fair Isle. They commanded that the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>'s bells be rung in celebration. Despite his celebrations, Jaehaerys did feel he should have been consulted, though he was less offended by this than the subsequent <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Wedding\" title=\"Golden Wedding\">union</a> of Queen Alyssa and Lord Rogar.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Although the wedding had apparently involved the traditional <a href=\"/index.php/Bedding\" title=\"Bedding\">bedding</a> ceremony,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> questions soon arose over whether Rhaena and Androw's marriage had actually been consummated. After the queen's party left Fair Isle for <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>, a castle <a href=\"/index.php/Septa\" title=\"Septa\">septa</a> asked Samantha Stokeworth if the marriage had ever been consummated and who had witnessed the bedding. Androw was considered a curious choice in spouse, given his status as an unpromising second son of a minor lord compared to her, a widowed Targaryen queen. Asked why she had chosen such an unpromising spouse, Rhaena would later reply, \"He was kind to me.\" Some suggested she took Androw as husband in part to repay Lord Marq for his kindness in offering refuge when Maegor ruled the Seven Kingdoms and the <a href=\"/index.php/Poor_Fellows\" title=\"Poor Fellows\">Poor Fellows</a> denounced her as a sinner. <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">Maester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Smike\" title=\"Smike\">Smike</a>, the master at Fair Isle, wrote that Rhaena found true love not with Androw but with his sister, Lady Elissa.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Attendees\">Attendees</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Attendees\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\"><img alt=\"House Farman.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/20px-House_Farman.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/30px-House_Farman.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/40px-House_Farman.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Androw_Farman\" title=\"Androw Farman\">Androw Farman</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\"><img alt=\"House Farman.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/20px-House_Farman.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/30px-House_Farman.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/40px-House_Farman.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Marq_Farman\" title=\"Marq Farman\">Marq Farman</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\"><img alt=\"House Farman.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/20px-House_Farman.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/30px-House_Farman.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/40px-House_Farman.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Elissa_Farman\" title=\"Elissa Farman\">Elissa Farman</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\"><img alt=\"House Lannister.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d5/House_Lannister.svg/20px-House_Lannister.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d5/House_Lannister.svg/30px-House_Lannister.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d5/House_Lannister.svg/40px-House_Lannister.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Lyman_Lannister\" title=\"Lyman Lannister\">Lyman Lannister</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\"><img alt=\"House Lannister.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d5/House_Lannister.svg/20px-House_Lannister.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d5/House_Lannister.svg/30px-House_Lannister.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d5/House_Lannister.svg/40px-House_Lannister.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jocasta_Lannister\" title=\"Jocasta Lannister\">Jocasta Lannister</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Stokeworth\" title=\"House Stokeworth\"><img alt=\"House Stokeworth.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/20px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/30px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/40px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Samantha_Stokeworth\" title=\"Samantha Stokeworth\">Samantha Stokeworth</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Royce\" title=\"House Royce\"><img alt=\"House Royce.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Royce.svg/20px-House_Royce.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Royce.svg/30px-House_Royce.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cf/House_Royce.svg/40px-House_Royce.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Alayne_Royce\" title=\"Alayne Royce\">Alayne Royce</a></li>\n<li>Bannermen and household knights to House Farman and House Lannister</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"